					<msContents>
						<summary>

						<p>States that <hi rend="bold">Sundara-Pāṇḍya</hi> defeated the Kēraḷa and Hoysaḷa kings and made his younger brother <hi rend="bold">Vīra-Pāṇḍya,</hi> the lord of <hi rend="bold">Koṅkaṇa-rājya.</hi> Refers also to the king's having performed the <hi rend="italic">Tulābhāra</hi> of gold and gilded the <hi rend="italic">vimāna</hi> of the temple. The inscription is in Sanskrit verse written in Grantha characters. The last verse of the record refers to the king as the elder brother of <hi rend="bold">Kulaśēkhara</hi> (vide, <hi rend="italic">A.R.Ep.,</hi> 1914, Part II, para. 19). Mentions Pārthasārathi <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Kōyil-Poṉmēynda-Perumāḷ-dāsaṉ. (See No. 199 below).</p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
